 distances\nusing LPVs. The majority of massive asymptotic giant branch (AGB) stars and red\nsupergiants form a smooth extension of sequence C of low- and intermediate-mass\nAGB stars in the P-Wrp diagram, suggesting that they pulsate in the fundamental\nmode. All results are similar in the two Magellanic Clouds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Sep 2019 16:45:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-16"}
